'''四脚弹跳'''（英文：'''stotting'''、'''pronking'''或'''pronging'''）是[[四足动物|四足动物]]的一种生活习性，尤其是[[瞪羚属|瞪羚属]] ，他们会四脚笔直地弹跳离开地面。通常，腿部都是相对僵直的，并且背部可以呈弓形，头部指向下。有证据表明，至少在某些情况下，它是一个告诉捕食者的{{link-en|诚实信号|honest signal|信号}}，告诉他自己不值得他们捕猎。

==发生==
四脚弹跳常发生在[[北美|北美]]的几种鹿种身上，比如[[騾鹿|騾鹿]]、[[叉角羚|叉角羚]]、<ref name="Roosevelt1905">{{cite book |last=Roosevelt |first=Theodore |year=1905 |title=Outdoor Pastimes of an American Hunter |url=https://archive.org/details/cu31924012115113 |publisher=C. Scribner's Sons }}</ref>以及[[黑尾鹿|黑尾鹿]]尤其是被捕食者威胁时，<ref>{{cite journal |last=Stankowich |first=Theodore |last2=Coss |first2=Richard |year=2007 |title=Effects of Risk Assessment, Predator Behavior, and Habitat on Escape Behavior in Columbian Black-Tailed Deer |journal=Behavioral Ecology |volume=18 |issue=2 |pages=358–367 |doi=10.1093/beheco/arl086 }}</ref>还有来自[[非洲|非洲]]的[[有蹄類|有蹄類]]动物，例如[[汤氏瞪羚|汤氏瞪羚]]和[[跳羚|跳羚]].<ref name="MaynardSmith"/>

四脚弹跳也会发生在驯化的[[牲畜|牲畜]]身上，例如[[绵羊|绵羊]]，但在牲畜中，它通常只在幼小的动物出现。<ref>{{cite book |title=Storey's Guide to Raising Sheep |last=Simmons |first=Paula |author2=Carol Ekarius  |year=2001 |publisher=Storey Publishing LLC |location=North Adams, MA |isbn=978-1-58017-262-2 }}</ref>

==可能的解释==
四脚弹跳使得猎物更显眼，<ref>{{cite journal | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=m5UYyI5YgokC&pg=PA34 | title=How the cheetah lost its stotts | author=Anon | journal=New Scientist |date=19 June 1986 | pages=34}}</ref>并消耗捕食者的时间和精力以便于逃离。由于动作危险，四脚弹跳必须给动物（或其家庭成员）带来一些好处。 已经提出了许多可能的解释。<ref name=Alcock>Alcock, J. (2009). ''Animal Behavior''. (Ninth ed.). Massachusetts: Sinauer Associates Inc.</ref><ref name=Caro>{{cite journal | url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0003347286800525 | title=The functions of stotting in Thomson’s gazelles: Some tests of the predictions | author=Caro, TM | journal=Animal Behaviour | year=1986 | volume=34 | pages=663–684 | doi=10.1016/S0003-3472(86)80052-5 | access-date=2016-12-31 | archive-date=2015-09-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924150703/http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0003347286800525 | dead-url=no }}</ref>它可能是：

#一种“快速逃脱或跳过障碍物”的好方法。<ref name="MaynardSmith">{{cite book | title=Animal Signals | publisher=Oxford University Press |author1=Maynard Smith, John |author2=Harper, David | year=2003 | pages=61–63 [https://books.google.com/books?id=SUA51MeG1lcC&pg=PA61&lpg=PA61]}}</ref><ref name=FitzFan>{{cite journal |url=http://webs.wofford.edu/moellerjf/Animal%20Behavior%202011/stotting%20in%20gazelles.pdf |title=Stotting in Thomson’s gazelles: an honest signal of condition |author1=FitzGibbon, CD |author2=Fanshawe, JH |journal=Behavioral Ecology and Sociobiology |date=August 1988 |volume=23 |issue=2 |pages=69–74 |doi=10.1007/bf00299889 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225073844/http://webs.wofford.edu/moellerjf/Animal%20Behavior%202011/stotting%20in%20gazelles.pdf |archivedate=2014-02-25 |access-date=2016-12-31 }}</ref> 
#[[反捕食者适应|反捕食者适应]]<ref name=Alcock/>
#对其他种成员发出“报警信号”，捕食者的接近很危险，为了增加畜群的存活率。{{efn|这是[[选择|选择]]或[[组选择|组选择]]的一个实例。}}<ref name=Alcock/>  
#一种“社会凝聚力”的行为，一起合作逃脱捕食者。<ref name=Alcock/> 
#被捕猎者的{{link-en|诚实信号|honest signal|信号}}。'''四脚弹跳可以通过警告食肉动物自己不适合作为猎物从而阻止追捕。<ref name=Alcock/><ref name=FitzFan/>
#一个{{link-en|Amotz Zahavi|Amotz Zahavi}}实例的{{link-en|差点原则|Handicap principle}}。<ref>{{cite book |first=Amotz |last=Zahavi |year=1997 |title=The Handicap Principle: A Missing Piece of Darwin's Puzzle |url=https://archive.org/details/handicapprincipl0000zeha |location=Oxford |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=0-19-510035-2 }}</ref>
#“捕食者检测信号”，由此动物向捕食者发出信号，借此希望捕食者捕捉自己从而放过别的同类。<ref name=Caro/><ref name=FitzFan/>
#在比[[反捕食者适应|反捕食者适应]]更能体验[[性选择|性选择]]的过程。<ref>[http://www.sa-lodges.com/articles/Herbivores-of-Pilanesberg.html Herbivores of the Pilanesberg National Park I] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sa-lodges.com/articles/Herbivores-of-Pilanesberg.html |date=20110715221436 }}, South African Lodges</ref>
#动物的[[玩耍|玩耍]]行为，尤其是年幼动物。<ref name=FitzFan/>
<references group="13" />

英国进化生物学家{{link-en|John Maynard Smith|John Maynard Smith}}的结论是：“自然的解释是，四脚弹跳逃跑能力的体现”，尤其是对捕食者的信号。他还指出，“这并不像是一个障碍”，除非是它对同一物种的其他瞪羚发出信号。<ref name="MaynardSmith" />

